<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06114025 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06114025 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  ARREST; SAN-LEANDRO; MAN; RAPE; ELDERLY; WOMAN; SAN-JOSE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A San Lorenzo man was arrested by San Jose police Monday minutes after heallegedly tried to rape a 70-year-old woman on Bascom Avenue near San CarlosStreet.;    Alvin Ross Smart, 50, was taken into custody shortly after 9:30a.m. because another woman several blocks away had called police to report asuspicious man lurking around the neighborhood, detective Mike McLaren said.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MAN ARRESTED IN S.J. ATTACK ON WOMAN, 70  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Officer Richard Gonzalez was shown the suspicious man's car, McLaren said,and waited nearby until the man returned to it.;    &quot;He was questioningSmart,&quot; McLaren said, &quot;when the report of the rape came over his pack radiowith the description of the suspect.&quot;;    Gonzalez radioed the officers takingthe assault report, and the victim was brought to where Smart was beingdetained.;    She identified Smart as her attacker, McLaren said.;    Thevictim told officers she had gone to her backyard shed after fetching hergarbage cans from the curb when someone came up behind her and put a hand overher mouth.;    &quot;He dragged her to the other side of the yard,&quot; McLaren said.&quot;He attempted to rape her but . . . she was resisting all the time.&quot;;    Theman got up and ran into the woman's house through her open back door but wasunable to unlock the key-bolted front door.;    He raced back out into theyard past the victim, who by now was yelling for help, and hurried down thedriveway.;    Smart, who gave his occupation as a professional chess player,has no criminal record in California, McLaren said.;    The victim was treatedat Valley Medical Center for minor injuries.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  BETTY BARNACLE, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910423  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  April  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  269  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday April 23, 199100114025,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>